a2t.text_actual: The Weather Channel app offers the best radar maps, local forecasts, & weather news available. With our app and widgets, you can enjoy the best day possible with the most accurate forecast available. After all, when you see the world through weather, It's Amazing Out There. Our favorite features include: •	Trusted forecasts include hourly, 36-hour, and 10-day forecast options (Celsius or Fahrenheit) •	Weather Maps: Fast, accurate, and localized radar maps offer past and future radar as well as severe weather alerts for storm tracking and tornado activity. With map layers you can select road or satellite views; activate hurricane tracking; and choose map layers, whether it’s cloud, radar, water temperature, wind speed, snow cover or more.   •	Current weather conditions give you the “feels like” temperature, sunrise time, sunset time, wind speed, humidity, UV index, visibility, dew point, and pressure.  •	Social Weather: Report your weather conditions to us! We'll use the information to improve the forecast & map out what others are reporting or tracking in your area. Plus, your report will be added to your personalized weather history, so you can track your past reports. To complete your report, remember to take a photo and share it with your friends. (MOBILE DEVICES ONLY) •	Severe Notifications and Weather Alerts: Get alerts for severe weather and high pollen counts for any of your favorite location(s). You also have the option to activate an always-on temperature in your notification bar for tracking the location of your choice. •	Weather Widgets: Offered in several sizes, whether you want the 1x1 weather widget, 2x2 weather widget, 4x1 weather widget, or 4x2 weather widget •	Seasonal tools, like our airport delays module, pollen counts, and boat & beach planner help you plan your life around the weather.  (MOBILE DEVICES ONLY) •	From severe storms to bizarre findings, stay up-to-date with the latest weather news stories. You can also watch our videos, which cover everything from your local forecast to climate change news. •	Beautiful and easy-to-use interface •	Amazing background photos match your location and current weather conditions. •	Navigation: swipe up and down to view the detailed forecasts and news stories.  •	The best weather app is also optimized for Android tablets  Don’t just listen to us! Here’s what the experts are saying about the best weather app: Gold Medal winner from Gizmodo’s best weather apps!   “Besides launching an impressive new look, a selection of social features have also been added to the application, radar maps are faster, and navigation has been enhanced. …” – App Advice   “… bright, crisp design and thoughtful layout. It packs a lot of information into not a lot of space, and a new social weather feature makes the service even more interactive … The Weather Channel is a deep dive into meteorological data...” – PC magazine   “One of the more intriguing new features is something The Weather Channel calls ‘Social Weather,’ … a native, Waze-like weather reporting service.” – TIME   "The Weather Channel app ... provides fast, accurate information.” – iDownloadBlog  THE WEATHER CHANNEL ON SOCIAL AND WEB: Check us out at weather.com, like us on facebook.com/theweatherchannel, and follow us on Twitter @weatherchannel for the latest breaking news and for tracking severe weather.
